umentiert erstmals Häuselmayers Bauten, die sich bei den Nutzern größter Beliebtheit erfreuen, da er mit Liebe zum Detail plant und zugleich den urbanen Kontext berücksichtigt.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aArchitecturezAustriaxHistoryy20th centuryvCatalogs. 0aArchitecturezAustriaxHistoryy21st centuryvCatalogs. 4aArchitekt. 4aStadtplanung. 4aWohnbau. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh1 aKristan, Markus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2018z9783110602999oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978303561543240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303561518040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035615180423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783035615180.jpg  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DADb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017